**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-ES-243 is currently contained in the High Value Intert Objects Wing of Site-34. The possible functioning anomalous properties of SCP-ES-243 are currently under study.

**Description:** SCP-ES-243 refers to an electromechanical device similar in appearance to a 64m^^2^^ soundproof booth, which was initially rusted and oxidized in appearance.

SCP-ES-243 is composed mainly of titanium, aluminum, and magnesium alloys, though more atypical materials have been found, including osmium, beryllium, chromium, and [[[scp-2046|a material as of yet unidentified by the Foundation]]].

SCP-ES-243's interior has several components with multiple control panels and a pair of elctromechanical terminals for operating them. However, it is currently impossible to do this, as the terminals are inoperative. Nonetheless, it is possible for data from both terminals to be retrieved from SCP-ES-243.

SCP-ES-243's front and multiple parts of its interior are inscribed with emblems of the Foundation and/or one of its Departments. However, there is no evidence of the Foundation contributing to SCP-ES-243's construction, nor being aware of its existence prior to its discovery.

Additional investigations are currently underway.

**Recovery Log:** On 11 November 1999, at 03:30, the SCP Observation Satellite //Jankovic// detected unusual disturbances in the [[[SCP-ES-154|Reality Gradient]]] in the Chihuahuan Desert, Chihuahua, Mexico. Approximately three minutes later, a 31,5km^^2^^ hole began to appear on the ground, releasing a large quantity of Disforming Radiation[[footnote]] Disforming Radiation is an anomalous phenomenon that is identifiable by the alteration of a Reality Gradient in a specific area, representing the presence of local reality imbalances. This type of radiation is invariably subsequent to a considerably powerful reality alterating event.[[/footnote]] that would dissipate unusually rapidly shortly after.

Due to the possibility of a topological or geological anonaly, Mobile Task Force [[[Task Forces#Zeta-9|Zeta-9 ("Mole Rats")]]] was deployed to the area to investigate and explore the formed crater. Zeta-9's initial mapping of the area uncovered an organized complex cave and tunnel system within the crater divided into nine levels.

SCP-ES-243 was discovered, with signs of having been frozen, at the crater's bottom. Subsequent analysis of the other eight levels revealed no signs of anomalous activity or other abnormalities.

**Addendum A:** Data from SCP-ES-243's terminals are transcribed below. Note that a large quantity of the data is corrupted. Efforts to restore these files are in progress.

